criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  CDC-diagnosed CFS-patients;

          -  female, between 18 and 59 years old;

          -  score of >40 on the subscale fatigue severity of the CIS (Checklist Individual
             Strength);

          -  marked functional impairment assessed with the Sickness Impact Profile (SIP-8) and
             operationalised as a total score of > 800.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnant or nursing women;

          -  women who intend to get pregnant during the study;

          -  patients who use or have used psychotropic medication in the past month;

          -  substance abuse in the past 3 months;

          -  patients taking any medication except oral contraceptives and/or paracetamol;

          -  patients with evident somatic co-morbidity;

          -  previous or current engagement in CFS research;

          -  inability to understand the nature and the extent of the trial and the procedure
             required;

          -  psychiatric co-morbidity assessed with the MINI;

          -  any condition, which in the opinion of the investigators might interfere with the
             evaluation of the study objects;

          -  current engagement in a legal procedure.
